Set the terminal into program mode
#iinncclluuddee <ccuurrsseess.hh>
ffiixxtteerrmm()

COHERENT  comes  with  a  set  of  functions  that  let  you  use  tteerrmmiinnffoo
descriptions to manipulate  a terminal.  ffiixxtteerrmm() restores the terminal to
its  internal conditions,  as  set by  the  ccuurrsseess/tteerrmmiinnffoo library.   Your
program should call ffiixxtteerrmm() after it returns from a shell escape.

